Get euchromatin regions

# 1. load and wrangle. note: undocumented bin-annotation: 2kb, centered
metadata_Hg38              <- fread("~/Downloads/RPE1_ChIC-orgins.tsv.gz")
metadata_Hg38$seqnames     <- metadata_Hg38$chr         # noob to BioC
metadata_Hg38$start        <- metadata_Hg38$round - 1e3 # sigh
metadata_Hg38$end          <- metadata_Hg38$round + 1e3 # sigh

# 2. life is too short for bad annotations
metadata_Hg38$measurement <- c("k27me3"  = "H3K27me3",
                               "k36me3"  = "H3K36me3", 
                               "k9me3"   = "H3K9me3", 
                               "nascent" = "nascent_transcription", 
                               "Meth"    = "DNAm", 
                               "Origins" = "replication_origin")[metadata_Hg38$variable]

# 3. only keep peaks 
metadata_Hg38 <- metadata_Hg38[smooth == 2]

# 4. to GR
metadata_Hg38 <- metadata_Hg38[,c('seqnames', 'start', 'end', 'measurement')]
metadata_Hg38 <- keepStandardChromosomes(makeGRangesFromDataFrame(metadata_Hg38, 
                                                                  keep.extra.columns = T),
                                         pruning.mode = 'coarse')
seqlevelsStyle(metadata_Hg38) <- "NCBI"
metadata_Hg38 <- split(metadata_Hg38, metadata_Hg38$measurement)

metadata_Hg38_raw_origins <- unique(metadata_Hg38$replication_origin)
metadata_Hg38 <- lapply(metadata_Hg38+1, reduce)

# 5. keep 2kb bins that have both H3K36me3 and nascent transcription
hg38_bins <- keepStandardChromosomes(tileGenome(seqlengths(BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38), 
                        tilewidth = 2e3, cut.last.tile.in.chrom = T),
                        pruning.mode = 'coarse')
seqlevelsStyle(hg38_bins) <- "NCBI"

hitlist <- lapply(metadata_Hg38, 
                  overlapsAny, query = hg38_bins, minoverlap = 1750)

euchromatic_regions <- reduce(hg38_bins[hitlist$nascent_transcription & 
                                          hitlist$H3K36me3])

# 6. plot reassurance
ROI <- GRanges('2:20000000-30000000')
toplot_metadata <- lapply(metadata_Hg38, function(e){
  as.data.frame(subsetByOverlaps(e, ROI))
  })
toplot_metadata <- as.data.frame(rbindlist(toplot_metadata,idcol = 'measurement'))
toplot_euchromatic <- as.data.frame(subsetByOverlaps(euchromatic_regions, ROI))
toplot_euchromatic$measurement <- "euchromatin"

p <- ggplot(rbind(toplot_metadata,toplot_euchromatic), 
       aes(xmin = start/1e6, xmax = end/1e6, ymin = 0, ymax = 1, 
           fill = measurement == 'euchromatin')) +
  geom_rect() +
  facet_wrap('measurement', ncol = 1) + 
  guides(fill = 'none') + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = rvdweide_pair_pal()(4)[c(1,4)]) +
  theme_rvdweide(box = T) + theme(axis.text.y = element_blank(),
                                  axis.ticks.y = element_blank()) +
  labs(x = 'chromosome 2', title = "Visual inspection for euchromatin calls")
p

# 7. to hg19
hg38_to_hg19_chain = import.chain(system.file(package="liftOver", 
                                              "extdata", 
                                              "hg38ToHg19.over.chain"))
euchromatic_regions_hg19 <- euchromatic_regions
seqlevelsStyle(euchromatic_regions_hg19) = "UCSC"  

euchromatic_regions_hg19 = reduce(unlist(liftOver(euchromatic_regions_hg19, 
                                           hg38_to_hg19_chain)))

Compute compartment-scores

# 1. calculate unsigned EVs
GSE71831_RPE1_WT_30$CS <- compartment_score(GSE71831_RPE1_WT_30)

# 2. sign compartment score
signbed <- as.data.frame(euchromatic_regions_hg19)[,1:3]
signbed$seqnames <- gsub('chr','',signbed$seqnames)
GSE71831_RPE1_WT_30$CS  <- sign_compartmentscore(GSE71831_RPE1_WT_30$CS, 
                                                 bed = signbed)

  plot_layout(ncol = 1, heights = c(7,1))

# 4. liftover to hg38
CS <- data.table(GSE71831_RPE1_WT_30$CS$compart_scores)
compartment_A <- reduce(makeGRangesFromDataFrame(CS[RPE1 > 0]))
compartment_B <- reduce(makeGRangesFromDataFrame(CS[RPE1 < 0]))
compartment_A <- compartment_A[width(compartment_A) > 1e6]
compartment_B <- compartment_B[width(compartment_B) > 1e6]


hg19_to_hg38_chain = import.chain("~/Downloads/hg19ToHg38.over.chain")
compartment_A_hg38 <- compartment_A
compartment_B_hg38 <- compartment_B
seqlevelsStyle(compartment_A_hg38) = "UCSC"  
seqlevelsStyle(compartment_B_hg38) = "UCSC"  

compartment_A_hg38 <- reduce(unlist(liftOver(compartment_A_hg38, 
                                           hg19_to_hg38_chain)))
compartment_B_hg38 <- reduce(unlist(liftOver(compartment_B_hg38, 
                                           hg19_to_hg38_chain)))
export.bed(compartment_A_hg38, '20230131_JvdB.RPE1.compartments/A_compartments_hg38.bed')
export.bed(compartment_B_hg38, '20230131_JvdB.RPE1.compartments/B_compartments_hg38.bed')

# 5. intersect CS and Origins
replication_origin <- metadata_Hg38_raw_origins
seqlevelsStyle(replication_origin) = "UCSC"  

A_origins <- unique(replication_origin[findOverlaps(replication_origin, 
                                       compartment_A_hg38)@from])
B_origins <- unique(replication_origin[findOverlaps(replication_origin, 
                                       compartment_B_hg38)@from])
export.bed(A_origins, '20230131_JvdB.RPE1.compartments/A_origins_hg38.bed')
export.bed(B_origins, '20230131_JvdB.RPE1.compartments/B_origins_hg38.bed')

rbind(data.table(compartment = 'A', 
           N_orgins = length(A_origins),
           N_origins_per_Mb_compartment = length(A_origins)/(sum(width(compartment_A_hg38))/1e6)),
data.table(compartment = 'B', 
           N_orgins = length(B_origins),
           N_origins_per_Mb_compartment = length(B_origins)/(sum(width(compartment_B_hg38))/1e6)))
